918799728754@c.us: What is human life expectancy in the United States?

The average life expectancy for a person born in the United States in 2019 is about 78.7 years, according to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC). This number is slightly higher for women at 81.1 years and lower for men at 76.1 years.
Who was president of the United States in 1955?
Dwight D. Eisenhower was the President of the United States in 1955. He was the 34th President of the United States, serving from 1953 to 1961.

A telescope works by collecting and magnifying distant light and making it easier for you to view objects in the night sky. It does this by using one or more curved lenses, a mirror, or a combination of both to reflect light from distant stars and galaxies. The combination of all components in a telescope, such as the lenses and mirror, create an image from a very distant object that is much larger, closer, and brighter then it would appear to the unaided eye.
